(44, 16, 1, 45, 16, 21, 21, NULL, 'Connection of Timothy''s Role', 'This connection highlights Timothy''s significance in early Christianity. Both passages reference Timothy, indicating his role as a disciple and a fellow worker in the ministry.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 2, 54, 5, 10, 10, 'well reported of', 'Connection of Good Reputation', 'Both passages emphasize being ''well reported of'' for good deeds. Acts 16:2 highlights a person''s positive reputation among brethren, while 1 Timothy 5:10 outlines specific good works that contribute to a woman''s commendable standing.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 2, 55, 3, 15, 15, 'well reported of by the brethren', 'Connection of Faith and Reputation', 'This connection highlights the importance of being well reported among believers, as seen in Acts, and the wisdom gained from scriptures in Timothy. Both passages emphasize the role of community and scripture in nurturing faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 2, 44, 6, 3, 3, NULL, 'Honest Report and Character', 'This connection highlights the importance of being ''of honest report'' in both passages. Acts 16:2 emphasizes the good reputation of Timothy, while Acts 6:3 calls for men of similar character to be appointed.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 2, 44, 13, 51, 51, 'brethren that were at Lystra and Iconium', 'Connection between Lystra and Iconium', 'This connection highlights the movement of Paul and his companions between Lystra and Iconium. The mention of Iconium in both passages emphasizes the significance of these locations in the early church''s mission.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 2, 54, 3, 7, 7, NULL, 'Good Report and Reputation', 'This connection highlights the importance of having a ''good report'' among both believers and outsiders. Both passages emphasize the necessity of a positive reputation to avoid reproach.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 2, 58, 11, 2, 2, 'well reported of by the brethren', 'Good Report Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of a ''good report'' in both passages. Acts 16:2 mentions a good reputation among brethren, while Hebrews 11:2 refers to elders obtaining a good report.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 3, 48, 2, 3, 3, 'because of the Jews which were in those quarters', 'Circumcision and Greek Identity', 'This connection highlights the differing attitudes towards circumcision in early Christianity. In Acts, Paul circumcises Timothy due to Jewish concerns, while in Galatians, Titus, a Greek, is not compelled to be circumcised.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 3, 46, 9, 20, 20, NULL, 'Paul''s Adaptation for Outreach', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s willingness to adapt his behavior to connect with different groups. In Acts, he circumcises Timothy to gain acceptance among the Jews, while in 1 Corinthians, he states he becomes as a Jew to win them over.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 3, 48, 5, 6, 6, NULL, 'Circumcision and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the act of circumcision in Acts and the emphasis on faith in Galatians. Both passages emphasize the significance of faith over physical rites, suggesting that true value lies in spiritual belief rather than adherence to the law.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 3, 44, 15, 20, 20, NULL, 'Cultural Considerations in Early Church', 'This connection highlights the cultural sensitivity of Paul in addressing Jewish customs, as seen in both passages. Acts 16:3 shows Paul''s decision to circumcise Timothy for the sake of the Jews, while Acts 15:20 outlines specific guidelines for Gentile believers to avoid offending Jewish traditions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 3, 44, 15, 40, 40, NULL, 'Paul''s Companionship in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s choice of companions for ministry. In Acts 16:3, Paul takes Timothy with him, while in Acts 15:40, he chooses Silas, highlighting the importance of partnerships in spreading the Gospel.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 3, 46, 7, 19, 19, NULL, 'Circumcision and Commandments Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrasting views on circumcision in early Christianity. Acts 16:3 shows Paul circumcising Timothy for the sake of Jewish acceptance, while 1 Corinthians 7:19 emphasizes that circumcision is irrelevant compared to obeying God''s commandments.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 4, 44, 15, 28, 29, 'decrees for to keep', 'Connection of Apostolic Decrees', 'This connection highlights the delivery of decrees from the apostles in Acts 16:4, which directly references the specific instructions given in Acts 15:28-29. Both passages emphasize the importance of these guidelines for the early church.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 4, 44, 15, 2, 2, 'the decrees for to keep', 'Connection of Apostolic Decrees', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the apostles and elders in making decisions for the early church. Acts 15:2 describes the gathering to discuss important matters, while Acts 16:4 refers to the delivery of those decisions to the cities.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 4, 44, 11, 30, 30, 'elders', 'Connection of Apostolic Decrees', 'Both passages emphasize the role of elders in the early church. Acts 16:4 refers to decrees delivered by apostles and elders, while Acts 11:30 mentions sending aid to the elders, highlighting their authority and responsibility.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 4, 44, 15, 6, 6, 'the apostles and elders', 'Connection of Apostolic Decrees', 'This connection highlights the role of the apostles and elders in making decisions for the early church. Both passages emphasize the authority of these leaders in guiding the community''s practices.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
